This paper is about a natural language processing task, specifically fact verification, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel graph attention network architecture, which involves learning from data and falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, such as evidence selection and reasoning, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves the use of kernel techniques, which is a common method in neural networks and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
